<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1939-02-28T08:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1939-02-28T08:00:00-05:00" n="781" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d781">
                                <note rend="inline" type="source">852.2221/1505: Telegram</note>
                                <head><hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Spain</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Bowers</hi></persName>), <hi rend="italic">Then in France, to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                                <opener>
                                    <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">St.
                                                Jean de Luz</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1939-02-28T13:00:00+00:00">February 28, 1939—1 p.m.</date><lb/>[Received 2:55
                                        p.m.]</dateline>
                                </opener>
                                <p>586. Marquis de Rialp has finally informed me that he is ready to
                                    deliver the 81 American prisoners at the frontier as soon as the
                                    Loyalists agree to an exchange. The situation of the Spanish
                                    Government is such just now as to make this difficult of
                                    realization but I am asking Del Vayo in Paris to transmit the
                                    proposition to Negrin.<note n="74" xml:id="d781fn74">Spanish
                                        Prime Minister.</note></p>
                                <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Bowers</hi></signed></closer>
                            </div>
                            </body></text></TEI>